&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="./plane.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="want-to-try"&gt;Want to try&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Swift&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Chisel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Haskell&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;TLA+ / Spin&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>X11 Forwarding from macOS</title><link>https://louieworth.github.io/personal/x11/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://louieworth.github.io/personal/x11/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="x11-forwarding-from-macos"&gt;X11 Forwarding from macOS&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what"&gt;What&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I want to install XQuartz on my Mac so that it has an X server, and then
forward it to remote hosts that I SSH onto.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why"&gt;Why&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So that I can run GUI applications on remote hosts without local X server
(or window manager). GUI apps on remote hosts will connect to the forwarded
X server on my Mac, and display whatever window directly on my Mac.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>